<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 4:22PM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Lincoln and
northwestern Cleveland Counties through 500 PM EDT...
At 422 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles north of Shelby, or near Casar, moving east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Belwood, Lawndale, Fallston, Polkville, Casar and Vale.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
